    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix signed/unsigned comparison in bfly5_tw1 radix-5 FFT butterfly\n\n### Summary\nThe radix-5 FFT butterfly function `bfly5_tw1` in the DFT implementation was not applying the same fixed-point scaling as the regular `bfly5` function when twiddle factors were set to 1. This caused incorrect magnitude scaling in the FFT output, leading to downstream signal processing errors.\n\nThis fix ensures `bfly5_tw1` applies identical scaling to `bfly5` by using `packed_cmult` with the W0 twiddle factor (representing 1.0 in Q15 format) for all input data before computation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Modified `bfly5_tw1` to apply proper fixed-point scaling\n\nWhen processing 5G NR uplink signals with radix-5 FFT sizes, users may observe:\n- Incorrect channel estimation magnitudes\n- PUSCH decoding failures with SNR > 20dB\n- PRACH detection false positives\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure eNB with 60 or 300 subcarrier DFT sizes\n2. Transmit PUSCH with high SNR (20dB+)\n3. Observe EVM > 10% in channel estimation despite clean channel conditions\n"
}